iran/","source_description":"Captured text from SafeAirspace Iran country risk page opened during arbitration investigation.","mime_type":"text/plain","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T13:56:00Z","relevance":"Aviation-risk context showing OIIX/Tehran FIR status, partial reopening/western closure in June 2026, and that major airspace restrictions were security-related rather than weather-related; also useful for adverse scope because it distinguishes partial reopening from full normal operations.","sha256":"b762826a22f06e9e298dc3d1a72573e68e7f5fbed102104e4af053c639890376","size_bytes":929},{"phase":"arguments","role":"plaintiff","evidence_id":"ev_51569ad0cb54_submitted-evidence-04-plaintiff-51569ad0cb54","name":"submitted-evidence-04-plaintiff-51569ad0cb54.txt","title":"EASA CZIB 2026-03-R13 Middle East airspace bulletin","source_url":"https://www.easa.europa.eu/en/domains/air-operations/czibs/2026-03-r13","source_description":"Captured text from official EASA conflict zone information bulletin page opened during arbitration investigation.","mime_type":"text/plain","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T13:56:00Z","relevance":"Official aviation authority context for non-weather security risk, affected Iranian airspace, and temporary airspace closures/restrictions by states during the conflict; corroborates that the relevant aviation disruptions were conflict/security related, not weather.","sha256":"51569ad0cb54f847f57c566a8aa45572ff0e4c29f8a8c22912b8a1b992b49ced","size_bytes":1592},{"phase":"arguments","role":"defendant","evidence_id":"ev_241b442bed15_submitted-evidence-05-defendant-241b442bed15","name":"submitted-evidence-05-defendant-241b442bed15.txt","title":"Notamify raw OIIX A1010/26 and A1015/26 NOTAM mirror","source_url":"https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/693f2d0f-54d3-433b-8128-49f5475ba269 and https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/67435351-52f9-4d17-8f4c-497a21dd94bf","source_description":"Captured text from public Notamify OIIX NOTAM pages opened during defendant arb